## Behavior Proof

All commands were run from WSL in `/root/src/openclaw-doctor-core-order` against isolated `/tmp/openclaw-doctor-proof-86627*` homes/configs. The local source CLI was invoked with `node --import tsx src/entry.ts` because the durable worktree did not have built `dist/` output.

`doctor --lint` with the Policy plugin enabled runs core checks and then extension/plugin checks:

```text
$ openclaw doctor --lint --json --only core/doctor/final-config-validation --only policy/policy-jsonc-missing
{"ok":false,"checksRun":2,"checksSkipped":55,"findings":[{"checkId":"policy/policy-jsonc-missing","severity":"warning","message":"policy.jsonc is missing for the enabled Policy plugin.","source":"policy","path":"policy.jsonc","fixHint":"Restore policy.jsonc or add the policy artifact for this workspace."}]}
```

The same lint selection path orders core contribution checks before plugin registry checks:

```text
core/doctor/gateway-config
core/doctor/claude-cli
core/doctor/gateway-auth
core/doctor/command-owner
core/doctor/legacy-state
...
{"total":57,"firstPlugin":18,"beforeFirstPlugin":"core/doctor/final-config-validation","firstPluginId":"policy/policy-jsonc-missing","lastKind":"plugin"}
```

Normal `doctor` completed against the isolated policy-enabled config and reported the existing legacy doctor notes, including gateway config/auth, plugin registry, state integrity, skills, gateway status, and `Doctor complete`.

`doctor --fix --non-interactive` completed against an isolated local-gateway config and preserved legacy repair behavior, including plugin registry rebuild, session store creation, skills disabling, config backup, config write, and `Doctor complete`.

## Updated In-Place Upgrade Stack

These are the doctor PRs already updated to take advantage of this model:

- #85566 - shell completion: structured lint health is owned by the existing `doctor:shell-completion` contribution.
- #84290 - UI freshness: structured lint/dry-run effects report missing/stale Control UI assets, while real build/rebuild stays on the existing doctor UI freshness path.
- #84366 - session locks: structured lint/dry-run effects report stale lock cleanup, while real cleanup stays on the existing session-lock doctor path.

The remaining older doctor repair PRs should be rebased onto this PR before they are presented as part of the same in-place upgrade series.
